name: Python
details: Python is a high-level, interpreted programming language known for its simplicity and readability.

name: JavaScript
details: JavaScript is a versatile, high-level programming language primarily used for web development to create interactive effects.

name: Java
details: Java is a widely-used, class-based, object-oriented programming language designed to have fewer implementation dependencies.

name: C#
details: C# is a modern, object-oriented programming language developed by Microsoft for building a variety of applications that run on the .NET Framework.

name: PHP
details: PHP is a popular general-purpose scripting language that is especially suited to web development.

name: Ruby
details: Ruby is a dynamic, open-source programming language with a focus on simplicity and productivity, known for its elegant syntax.

name: Swift
details: Swift is a powerful and intuitive programming language for macOS, iOS, watchOS, and tvOS app development.

name: Kotlin
details: Kotlin is a modern, statically typed programming language used for developing Android apps and is fully interoperable with Java.

name: TypeScript
details: TypeScript is a strongly typed programming language that builds on JavaScript, giving you better tooling at any scale.

name: Go
details: Go, also known as Golang, is an open-source programming language designed for simplicity and reliability, particularly in system programming.

name: ReactJS
details: ReactJS is a JavaScript library for building user interfaces, maintained by Facebook and a community of developers.

name: Angular
details: Angular is a platform for building mobile and desktop web applications, developed by Google.

name: Vue.js
details: Vue.js is a progressive JavaScript framework used for building user interfaces and single-page applications.

name: Django
details: Django is a high-level Python web framework that encourages rapid development and clean, pragmatic design.

name: Spring
details: Spring is a comprehensive framework for enterprise Java development, providing infrastructure support for developing Java applications.

name: Laravel
details: Laravel is a PHP framework for web artisans, providing an elegant syntax and a robust set of tools for web development.

name: Node.js
details: Node.js is a JavaScript runtime built on Chrome's V8 JavaScript engine, enabling server-side scripting and building scalable network applications.

name: Flask
details: Flask is a lightweight WSGI web application framework in Python, designed to be quick and easy to use for small to medium applications.

name: Ruby on Rails
details: Ruby on Rails is a server-side web application framework written in Ruby under the MIT License, focusing on convention over configuration.

name: ASP.NET
details: ASP.NET is an open-source server-side web application framework designed for web development to produce dynamic web pages, developed by Microsoft.
